eTeam is a global company with offices in the US, Ukraine, and Mexico specializing in building custom software for enterprise clients and VC-backed startups across the US, UK, Germany, Japan, and Indonesia. In five years, we have grown to a team of over 100 employees worldwide, become a certified AWS Consulting partner, and have been named a global Clutch Leader for three years in a row. Recently we were ranked in the Inc. 5000 list.

We look for curious, creative people who work to be a little better every day. In our work together, we embody our values: Teamwork, Curiosity, Accountability and Integrity.

As a marketing specialist, you will be responsible for executing marketing strategy, coordinating with a sales department to develop and monitor marketing initiatives and aligning company positioning across various platforms.

Responsibilities:
Develop, implement, and track marketing programs such as email, social media, or digital campaigns;
Collaborate with other internal teams (e.g. product and sales) to develop and monitor strategic marketing initiatives;
Deliver marketing campaigns, analyze and report on their performance and efficiency;
Identify new opportunities for growth and expansion by analysis of marketing data, including campaign results, conversion rates and online traffic;
Develop and create marketing materials, such as sales and product collateral, and ensure brand guidelines are met;
Write, proofread, and edit creative and technical content across the company website, social media and other marketing platforms;
Work with external agencies and vendors to execute marketing programs.

Requirements:
3+ years of digital marketing experience in a software development company;
Strong understanding of key marketing concepts, such as market segmentation, value proposition, differentiation, and branding;
Proven ability to build the marketing funnel and user journey;
Experience with social media and digital marketing tools and platforms, including email marketing and website management;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams;
Fluent English.

Will be a plus:
Work experience in software development service companies.

We offer:
Grow professionally with subsidized certifications, courses, and conferences;
Improve your English with conversation clubs and direct client communication;
Remote work, flexible schedule, bonuses for important life events.

